CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 NAME
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    CorScorer: Perl package for scoring coreference resolution systems
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    using different metrics.


CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 VERSION
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    v8.01 -- reference implementations of MUC, B-cubed, CEAF and BLANC metrics.


CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 CHANGES SINCE v8.0
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    - fixed a bug that crashed the BLANC scorer when a duplicate singleton
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      mention was present in the response.

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 INSTALLATION
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Requirements:
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201       1. Perl: downloadable from http://perl.org
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201       2. Algorithm-Munkres: included in this package and downloadable
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201          from CPAN http://search.cpan.org/~tpederse/Algorithm-Munkres-0.08

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 USE
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    This package is distributed with two scripts to execute the scorer from
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    the command line.

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Windows (tm): scorer.bat
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Linux: scorer.pl


CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 SYNOPSIS
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    use CorScorer;

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    $metric = 'ceafm';

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    # Scores the whole dataset
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    &CorScorer::Score($metric, $keys_file, $response_file);

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    # Scores one file
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    &CorScorer::Score($metric, $keys_file, $response_file, $name);


CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 INPUT
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    metric: the metric desired to score the results:
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      muc: MUCScorer (Vilain et al, 1995)
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      bcub: B-Cubed (Bagga and Baldwin, 1998)
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      ceafm: CEAF (Luo et al., 2005) using mention-based similarity
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      ceafe: CEAF (Luo et al., 2005) using entity-based similarity
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      blanc: BLANC (Luo et al., 2014) BLANC metric for gold and predicted mentions
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      all: uses all the metrics to score

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    keys_file: file with expected coreference chains in CoNLL-2011/2012 format

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    response_file: file with output of coreference system (CoNLL-2011/2012 format)

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    name: [optional] the name of the document to score. If name is not
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      given, all the documents in the dataset will be scored. If given
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      name is "none" then all the documents are scored but only total
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201      results are shown.


CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201 OUTPUT
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    The score subroutine returns an array with four values in this order:
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    1) Recall numerator
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    2) Recall denominator
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    3) Precision numerator
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    4) Precision denominator

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Also recall, precision and F1 are printed in the standard output when variable
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    $VERBOSE is not null.

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Final scores:
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Recall = recall_numerator / recall_denominator
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Precision = precision_numerator / precision_denominator
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    F1 = 2 * Recall * Precision / (Recall + Precision)

CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Identification of mentions
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    An scorer for identification of mentions (recall, precision and F1) is also included.
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    Mentions from system response are compared with key mentions. This version performs
CESS-CAT-AAP_98_20001201    strict mention matching as was used in the CoNLL-2011 and 2012 shared tasks.

